Note:
TOKEN_CONSTANTS - the single canonical registry of lexer/parser token types.

This module is the ONE authoritative definition of every TOKEN_* code. Every
lexical and parsing module imports it instead of declaring its own copies; the
import system merges these constants into each importer's symbol table so that
a bare reference such as TOKEN_PLUS resolves here and the compiler inlines the
canonical value. Centralizing the codes guarantees the lexer and the parser
agree on every token type - the prerequisite for the modular frontend to
tokenize and parse correctly when all modules are linked into one binary.

Numbering is organized in blocks by category (literals, delimiters, keywords,
operators, ...). Synonym names that denote the same token (e.g. TOKEN_STRING /
TOKEN_STRING_LITERAL, the three f-string spellings, TOKEN_ASSIGN / TOKEN_EQUALS)
intentionally share a value; every distinct token has a unique value.
:End Note

